    <fr:title text="Construct addition operator on the set of Dedekind cuts">Construct addition operator on the set of Dedekind cuts</fr:title>
    <fr:meta name="source"><fr:link href="/baby-rudin/" title="Principles of Mathematical Analysis" uri="http://localhost:8000/baby-rudin/" display-uri="baby-rudin" type="local">Principles of Mathematical Analysis</fr:link>, Appendix to Ch. 1</fr:meta>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex> be the set of all <fr:link href="/ca-000U/" title="Dedekind cuts" uri="http://localhost:8000/ca-000U/" display-uri="ca-000U" type="local">Dedekind cuts</fr:link>. Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpa ,\beta \in  R]]></fr:tex>. We will define the set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha +\beta =\{r+s\mid  r\in \alpha ,s\in \beta \}]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
    <html:p>For the sake of clarity, we will denote <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[0_{R}]]></fr:tex> to be the set of all negative rational numbers. We see <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[0_{R}]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="/ca-000U/" title="Dedekind cuts" uri="http://localhost:8000/ca-000U/" display-uri="ca-000U" type="local">Dedekind cuts</fr:link>. We claim <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[0_{R}]]></fr:tex> acts like the "zero" of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
    <html:p><html:strong>Claim 1:</html:strong> For any <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha ,\beta \in  R]]></fr:tex>, we see <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha +\beta ]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="/ca-000U/" title="Dedekind cuts" uri="http://localhost:8000/ca-000U/" display-uri="ca-000U" type="local">Dedekind cuts</fr:link>.</html:p>
    <html:p><html:strong>Claim 2:</html:strong> For any <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha ,\beta \in  R]]></fr:tex>, we see <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha +\beta =\beta +\alpha ]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
    <html:p><html:strong>Claim 3:</html:strong> For any <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha ,\beta ,\gamma \in  R]]></fr:tex>, we see <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(\alpha +\beta )+\gamma =\alpha +(\beta +\gamma )]]></fr:tex></html:p>
    <html:p><html:strong>Claim 4:</html:strong> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[0_{R}\in  R]]></fr:tex> and for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha \in  R]]></fr:tex>, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[0_{R}+\alpha =\alpha ]]></fr:tex></html:p>
    <html:p><html:strong>Claim 5:</html:strong> To every <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha \in  R]]></fr:tex> there exists an <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[-\alpha \in  R]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha +(-\alpha )=0_{R}]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
